Plague's Caress		KEY:Pestilence Bloodline ~ Plague's Caress			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Sorcerer Class Feature.Pestilence Bloodline ~ Power LVL 01.Sorcerer Bloodline Power.SpecialAttack.SpellLike				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sorcerer Bloodline ~ Pestilence	PREVARGTEQ:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlineProgressionLVL,1	DEFINE:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlinePower1LVL|0	DEFINE:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlinePower1Times|0		DESC:At 1st level, you can make a melee touch attack as a standard action that causes a living creature’s flesh to break out into rancid-smelling pustules and sores for a number of rounds equal to 1/2 your sorcerer level (minimum 1 round). These sores cause the victim to become sickened for the duration of the effect; this is a disease effect. You can use this ability a number of times per day equal to %1 times per day.|Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlinePower1Times		SOURCEPAGE:p.29	ASPECT:CheckCount|%1|Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlinePower1Times	ASPECT:CheckType|Uses per Day	ASPECT:ChildAbility|PestilenceBloodlinePowers
Accustomed to Awfulness	KEY:Pestilence Bloodline ~ Accustomed to Awfulness		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Sorcerer Class Feature.Pestilence Bloodline ~ Power LVL 03.Sorcerer Bloodline Power.SpecialAttack.Special Attack.Extraordinary			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sorcerer Bloodline ~ Pestilence	PREVARGTEQ:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlineProgressionLVL,3	DEFINE:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlinePower3LVL|0																																					DESC:At 3rd level, you become immune to the sickened condition and gain a +4 bonus on all saving throws against effects that cause nausea or disease. At 9th level, you become immune to the nauseated condition and to the debilitating effects of disease (but you can still be a carrier of diseases).	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	ASPECT:ChildAbility|PestilenceBloodlinePowers
Shroud of Vermin		KEY:Pestilence Bloodline ~ Shroud of Vermin			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Sorcerer Class Feature.Pestilence Bloodline ~ Power LVL 09.Sorcerer Bloodline Power.SpecialQuality.Supernatural						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sorcerer Bloodline ~ Pestilence	PREVARGTEQ:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlineProgressionLVL,9	DEFINE:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlinePower9LVL|0			DESC:At 9th level, swarms no longer see you as prey. You can walk among swarms without fear of being harmed by them at all, and by taking a standard action to mentally command a swarm in which you stand, you can direct that swarm’s attacks and movements as long as you have more Hit Dice than the swarm. Even when you aren’t standing amid a swarm, your body crawls with vermin, and their chitinous bodies increase your natural armor bonus by +1. At 11th level, this bonus increases to +2, and at 17th level it increases to +3.	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	ASPECT:ChildAbility|PestilenceBloodlinePowers
Pestilential Breath	KEY:Pestilence Bloodline ~ Pestilential Breath			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Sorcerer Class Feature.Pestilence Bloodline ~ Power LVL 15.Sorcerer Bloodline Power.SpecialQuality.Supernatural						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sorcerer Bloodline ~ Pestilence	PREVARGTEQ:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlineProgressionLVL,15	DEFINE:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlinePower15LVL|0		DESC:At 15th level, the sickness within your body finally becomes so potent that your very breath is deadly. Once per day as a standard action, you can exhale a cloud of pestilence in a 30-foot cone. Those caught in the area of this miasmic cloud receive a single Fortitude save to avoid suffering the effects of two different diseases. The DC of this save is equal to 10 + 1/2 your sorcerer level + your Charisma modifier. You can choose what two diseases you inflict on each target that succumbs to your plague breath, but they must be two different diseases chosen from the following list: blinding sickness, bubonic plague, cackle fever, filth fever, leprosy, mindfire, red ache, shakes, or slimy doom. The victim suffers the initial effects of these two diseases immediately—use the diseases’ frequency and save DC normally to determine further effects as detailed on page 557 of the Pathfinder RPG Core Rulebook. At 17th level, you can use this ability twice per day. At 20th level you can use this ability three times per day.	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	ASPECT:ChildAbility|PestilenceBloodlinePowers
Plague Carrier		KEY:Pestilence Bloodline ~ Plague Carrier				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Sorcerer Class Feature.Pestilence Bloodline ~ Power LVL 20.Sorcerer Bloodline Power.SpecialQuality.Supernatural						PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sorcerer Bloodline ~ Pestilence	PREVARGTEQ:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlineProgressionLVL,20	DEFINE:Sorcerer_Pestilence_BloodlinePower20LVL|0		DESC:At 20th level, your touch inflicts mummy rot on those you strike. You can choose to suppress this ability for 1 round as a swift action. You can make a touch attack to inflict this disease on a target, or transfer it as part of an attack with any melee weapon or touch-based spell. The creature touched can resist contracting mummy rot by making a Fortitude save—the DC is equal to 10 + 1/2 your sorcerer level + your Charisma modifier.	SOURCEPAGE:p.30	ASPECT:ChildAbility|PestilenceBloodlinePowers
